quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  21,83,"And Job -- when he called unto his Lord, 'Behold, affliction has visited me, and Thou art the most merciful of the merciful"
  21,84,"So We answered him, and removed the affliction that was upon him, and We gave his people, and the like of them with them, mercy from Us, and a Reminder to those who serve"
  21,85,"And Ishmael, Idris, Dhul Kifl -- each was of the patient"
  21,86,and We admitted them into Our mercy; they were of the righteous
  21,87,"And Dhul Nun -- when he went forth enraged and thought that We would have no power over him; then he called out in the darkness, 'There is no god but Thou. Glory be to Thee! I have done evil"
  21,88,"So We answered him, and delivered him out of grief; even so do, We deliver the believers"
  21,89,"And Zachariah -- when he called unto his Lord, 'O my Lord, leave me not solitary; though Thou art the best of inheritors"
  21,90,"So We answered him, and bestowed on him John, and We set his wife right for him; truly they vied with one another, hastening to good works, and called upon Us out of yearning and awe; and they were humble to Us"
  21,91,"And she who guarded her virginity, so We breathed into her of Our spirit and appointed her and her son to be a sign unto all beings"
  21,92,"Surely this community of yours is one community, and I am your Lord; so serve Me"
  21,93,But they split up their affair between them; all shall return to Us
  21,94,"And whosoever does deeds of righteousness, being a believer, no unthankfulness shall befall his endeavour; We Ourselves write it down for him"
  21,95,There is a ban upon any city that We have destroyed; they shall not return
  21,96,"till, when Gog and Magog are unloosed, and they slide down out of every slope"
  21,97,"and nigh has drawn the true promise, and behold, the eyes of the unbelievers staring: 'Alas for us! We were heedless of this; 'nay, we were evildoers"
  21,98,"Surely you, and that you were serving apart from God, are fuel for Gehenna; you shall go down to it"
  21,99,"If those had been gods, they would never have gone down to it; yet every one of them shall therein abide forever"
  21,100,"there shall be sighing for them therein, and naught they shall hear"
  21,101,But as for those unto whom already the reward most fair has gone forth from Us
  21,102,"they shall be, kept far from it neither shall they hear any whisper of it, and they shall dwell forever in that their souls desired"
  21,103,"the greatest terror shall not grieve them, and the angels shall receive them: 'This is your day that you were promised"
  21,104,"On the day when We shall roll up heaven as a scroll is rolled for the writings; as We originated the first creation, so We shall bring it back again -- a promise binding on Us; so We shall do"
  21,105,"For We have written in the Psalms, after the Remembrance, 'The earth shall be the inheritance of My righteous servants"
  21,106,Surely in this is a Message delivered unto a people who serve
  21,107,"We have not sent thee, save as a mercy unto all beings"
  21,108,"Say: 'It is revealed unto me only that your God is One God; do you then surrender"
  21,109,"Then, if they should turn their backs, say: 'I have proclaimed to you all equally, even though I know not whether near or far is that you are promised"
  21,110,Surely He knows what is spoken aloud and He knows what you hide
  21,111,I know not; haply it is a trial for you and an enjoyment for a time
  21,112,"He said: 'My Lord, judge Thou with truth! And our Lord is the All-merciful; His succour is ever to be sought against that you describe"